#. <section class="sutta" id="sn56.41"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.41:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.41:0.2"
msgid "5. Papātavagga"
msgstr "5. A Cliff"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 41. Lokacintāsutta → cintāsuttaṃ (bj) | cintā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.41:0.3"
msgid "41. Lokacintāsutta"
msgstr "41. Speculation About the World"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.447"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.41:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, in the Bamboo Grove, the "
"squirrels’ feeding ground."

msgctxt "sn56.41:1.2"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

#. VAR: sumāgadhā → sumāgavā (bj)
msgctxt "sn56.41:1.3"
msgid ""
"“bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, aññataro puriso rājagahā nikkhamitvā ‘lokacintaṃ "
"cintessāmī’ti yena sumāgadhā pokkharaṇī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"sumāgadhāya pokkharaṇiyā tīre nisīdi lokacintaṃ cintento."
msgstr ""
"“Once upon a time, mendicants, a certain person left Rājagaha, thinking ‘I’"
"ll speculate about the world.’ They went to the Sumāgadhā lotus pond and sat "
"down on the bank speculating about the world."

#. VAR: caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ → pokkharaṇiyā caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ (bj) | caturaṅginisenaṃ (mr)
#. VAR: bhisamuḷālaṃ → bhisamūḷālaṃ (pts1) | bhisamūlālaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn56.41:1.4"
msgid ""
"Addasā kho, bhikkhave, so puriso sumāgadhāya pokkharaṇiyā tīre caturaṅginiṃ "
"senaṃ bhisamuḷālaṃ pavisantaṃ."
msgstr "Then that person saw an army of four divisions enter a lotus stalk."

msgctxt "sn56.41:1.5"
msgid "Disvānassa etadahosi:"
msgstr "When he saw this he thought:"

msgctxt "sn56.41:1.6"
msgid "‘ummattosmi nāmāhaṃ, vicetosmi nāmāhaṃ."
msgstr "‘I’ve gone mad, really, I’ve lost my mind!"

msgctxt "sn56.41:1.7"
msgid "Yaṃ loke natthi taṃ mayā diṭṭhan’ti."
msgstr "I’m seeing things that don’t exist in the world.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.41:2.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho so, bhikkhave, puriso nagaraṃ pavisitvā mahājanakāyassa ārocesi:"
msgstr "Then that person entered the city and informed a large crowd:"

msgctxt "sn56.41:2.2"
msgid "‘ummattosmi nāmāhaṃ, bhante, vicetosmi nāmāhaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "‘I’ve gone mad, really, I’ve lost my mind!"

msgctxt "sn56.41:2.3"
msgid "Yaṃ loke natthi taṃ mayā diṭṭhan’ti."
msgstr "I’m seeing things that don’t exist in the world.’"

msgctxt "sn56.41:2.4"
msgid "‘Kathaṃ pana tvaṃ, ambho purisa, ummatto kathaṃ viceto?"
msgstr "‘But how is it that you’re mad? How have you lost your mind?"

msgctxt "sn56.41:2.5"
msgid "Kiñca loke natthi yaṃ tayā diṭṭhan’ti?"
msgstr "And what have you seen that doesn’t exist in the world?’"

msgctxt "sn56.41:2.6"
msgid ""
"‘Idhāhaṃ, bhante, rājagahā nikkhamitvā “lokacintaṃ cintessāmī”ti yena "
"sumāgadhā pokkharaṇī tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā sumāgadhāya pokkharaṇiyā "
"tīre nisīdiṃ lokacintaṃ cintento."
msgstr ""
"‘Sirs, I left Rājagaha, thinking “I’ll speculate about the world.” I went to "
"the Sumāgadhā lotus pond and sat down on the bank speculating about the "
"world."

msgctxt "sn56.41:2.7"
msgid ""
"Addasaṃ khvāhaṃ, bhante, sumāgadhāya pokkharaṇiyā tīre caturaṅginiṃ senaṃ "
"bhisamuḷālaṃ pavisantaṃ."
msgstr "Then I saw an army of four divisions enter a lotus stalk."

msgctxt "sn56.41:2.8"
msgid "Evaṃ khvāhaṃ, bhante, ummatto evaṃ viceto."
msgstr "That’s why I’m mad, that’s why I’ve lost my mind."

msgctxt "sn56.41:2.9"
msgid "Idañca loke natthi yaṃ mayā diṭṭhan’ti."
msgstr "And that’s what I’ve seen that doesn’t exist in the world.’"

msgctxt "sn56.41:2.10"
msgid "‘Taggha tvaṃ, ambho purisa, ummatto taggha viceto."
msgstr "‘Well, mister, you’re definitely mad, you’ve definitely lost your mind."

msgctxt "sn56.41:2.11"
msgid "Idañca loke natthi yaṃ tayā diṭṭhan’ti."
msgstr "And you’re seeing things that don’t exist in the world.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli5.448"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.41:3.1"
msgid "Taṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, so puriso bhūtaṃyeva addasa, no abhūtaṃ."
msgstr "But what that person saw was in fact real, not unreal."

msgctxt "sn56.41:3.2"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, devāsurasaṅgāmo samupabyūḷho ahosi."
msgstr "Once upon a time, a battle was fought between the gods and the demons."

msgctxt "sn56.41:3.3"
msgid "Tasmiṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, saṅgāme devā jiniṃsu, asurā parājiniṃsu."
msgstr "In that battle the gods won and the demons lost."

msgctxt "sn56.41:3.4"
msgid ""
"Parājitā ca kho, bhikkhave, asurā bhītā bhisamuḷālena asurapuraṃ pavisiṃsu "
"devānaṃyeva mohayamānā."
msgstr ""
"The defeated and terrified demons entered the demon city through the lotus "
"stalk only to confuse the gods."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.41:4.1"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, mā lokacintaṃ cintetha:"
msgstr "So mendicants, don’t speculate about the world."

msgctxt "sn56.41:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘sassato loko’ti vā ‘asassato loko’ti vā, ‘antavā loko’ti vā ‘anantavā loko’"
"ti vā, ‘taṃ jīvaṃ taṃ sarīran’ti vā ‘aññaṃ jīvaṃ aññaṃ sarīran’ti vā, ‘hoti "
"tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā ‘na hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘hoti ca "
"na ca hoti tathāgato paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā, ‘neva hoti na na hoti tathāgato "
"paraṃ maraṇā’ti vā."
msgstr ""
"For example: the world is eternal, or not eternal, or finite, or infinite; "
"the soul and the body are the same thing, or they are different things; "
"after death, a Realized One exists, or doesn’t exist, or both exists and "
"doesn’t exist, or neither exists nor doesn’t exist."

msgctxt "sn56.41:4.3"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn56.41:4.4"
msgid ""
"Nesā, bhikkhave, cintā atthasaṃhitā nādibrahmacariyakā na nibbidāya na "
"virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya "
"saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"Because those ideas aren’t beneficial or relevant to the fundamentals of the "
"spiritual life. They don’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, "
"peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.41:5.1"
msgid ""
"Cintentā kho tumhe, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti cinteyyātha … pe … ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti cinteyyātha."
msgstr ""
"When you think something up, you should think: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This "
"is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This "
"is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’."

msgctxt "sn56.41:5.2"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn56.41:5.3"
msgid ""
"Esā, bhikkhave, cintā atthasaṃhitā esā ādibrahmacariyakā esā nibbidāya "
"virāgāya nirodhāya upasamāya abhiññāya sambodhāya nibbānāya saṃvattati."
msgstr ""
"Because those ideas are beneficial and relevant to the fundamentals of the "
"spiritual life. They lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, "
"insight, awakening, and extinguishment."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.41:6.1"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti."
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.41:6.2"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
